ralize these shape\noperations to shape anisotropy dimensions, in analogy with the anisotropy\ndimensions introduced for enthalpically patchy particles. Our findings\ndemonstrate that entropic patchiness and emergent valence provide a way of\nengineering directional bonding into nanoparticle systems, whether in the\npresence or absence of additional, non-entropic forces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Apr 2013 00:55:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 13 Feb 2014 21:29:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-02-18"}
