ycle 23. The decline in fields\nabove $\\pm45{^{\\circ}}$ for well over a solar cycle, would imply that weak\npolar fields have been generated in the past two successive solar cycles\n\\textit{viz.} cycles 22 and 23. A continuation of this declining trend beyond\n22 years, if it occurs, will have serious implications on our current\nunderstanding of the solar dynamo.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 28 Apr 2013 16:04:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
